
--- Secondary storage ---
Configure an additional local path for redundant copies.
IMPORTANT: Secondary path must be a filesystem-mounted directory (e.g., /mnt/nas-backup)
Network shares must be mounted BEFORE running this backup tool.
For direct network access without mounting, use cloud storage (rclone) instead.
(You can change these settings later in backup.env)
Enable secondary backup path? [y/N]: 
--- Cloud storage (rclone) ---
Remember to configure rclone manually before enabling cloud backups.
Enable cloud backups? [y/N]: 
--- Firewall rules ---
Enable collection of firewall rules (e.g., iptables/nftables).
(You can change this later in backup.env via BACKUP_FIREWALL_RULES)
Backup firewall rules? [y/N]: 
--- Telegram ---
Enable Telegram notifications (centralized)? [y/N]: 
--- Email ---
Default email delivery uses the ProxSave Cloud Relay, with local sendmail as failover.
ProxSave does not collect raw SMTP settings; choose pmf only when Proxmox Notifications is configured.
Enable email notifications? [y/N]: 
--- Encryption ---
Enable backup encryption? [y/N]: 
--- Scheduler ---
Scheduler engine: daemon (resident, hang watchdog + healthchecks) or cron [daemon]: 
--- Backup monitoring (healthchecks) ---
off         no monitoring
centralized ProxSave HC Server (zero setup, reuses the Telegram identity)
self        your own healthchecks/SaaS server (you paste the ping URLs next)
Healthchecks monitoring: off, centralized, or self [centralized]: 
